1
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:16,600
Fate is woven by three forces.

2
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:21,960
However, the fate of some is made to be
more complicated than that.

3
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,240
My sister will be back to normal, won’t she?

4
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:26,760
Once you can control the Six-Eared,

5
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:28,400
we’ll begin sealing Qi Rong right away.

6
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,120
Why were you born, Pete?

7
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:30,440
Why?

8
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:31,840
This is all just the voices in my head!

9
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,600
You have the demon under control.

10
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,040
CONFIRMING SOUL BINDING RITUAL

11
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,000
DEAR MASTER NIRAN,
WE’VE DECIDED WE WANT YOU

12
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:02,800
PLEASE LET US KNOW
WHEN YOU CAN DO IT.

13
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:03,400
So…

14
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:06,080
Now that the seal is undone, what’s next?

15
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:08,360
How do I use the demon’s power?

16
00:01:10,160 --> 00:01:11,480
I think you should take a rest for today.

17
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:14,520
Its power is already within you.

18
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,480
TOMORROW’S FINE.

19
00:01:16,640 --> 00:01:18,520
The hardest part is over.

20
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:23,400
But you can think about what kind of things
you want to hear and give it a try.

21
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,640
(Crap! They’re everywhere!)

22
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:49,920
(Give me more booze!)

23
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:51,240
(Come on!)

24
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,080
(Jack, Jack!)

25
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,080
(Tao, hold up!)

26
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,720
(Jack, come on!)

27
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:19,880
(Fill in!)

28
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,640
Bottoms up!

29
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:57,120
I’m doing my best here!

30
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,280
They’re everywhere!

31
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,160
What are you doing?

32
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:17,360
There’s a couple.

33
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,000
One of them is filthy rich.

34
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,560
They’re hiring me to perform
a soul binding ritual.

35
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:26,320
I’m amazed you have the energy to work
on the side at a time like this.

36
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:27,960
It’s simple enough.

37
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,160
Takes no more than a few minutes.

38
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,960
For two million, too.

39
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,240
Why wouldn’t I do it?

40
00:04:33,159 --> 00:04:35,200
Well, if you’re a money-hungry idiot,

41
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,440
I’d understand.

42
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:41,440
But no, you don’t buy mansions.

43
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,960
You drive an old car.

44
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:48,720
What are you even making millions
of money for if you’re not spending it?

45
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,000
Niran.

46
00:04:56,159 --> 00:04:58,040
because I work for a politician.

47
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,880
I know people call me a government lapdog

48
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,080
But I have a goal.

49
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,480
The path I walk isn’t paved
with rose petals.

50
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:14,120
But at least I’m doing something for others.

51
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,640
For our country.

52
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,640
For people like me.

53
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:22,160
For people like us.

54
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:25,880
Yes.

55
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:31,400
Our getting involved in politics
may be considered an intervention.

56
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:35,480
But I’m certain I’m not defying
the will of heaven.

57
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,080
What about you, Niran?

58
00:05:39,159 --> 00:05:40,280
Can you give me a reason?

59
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,560
Why did you choose to be an outcast?

60
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:45,600
What are you up against?

61
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:49,000
See?

62
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:51,840
You’re always like this.

63
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,080
Don’t you understand why I’m so worried about you?

64
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,159
I’m helping people secure their one true love.

65
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,760
Isn’t that a good thing?

66
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,760
As long as it doesn’t defy heaven.

67
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:08,560
Even heaven can’t stop
two people from falling in love.

68
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:12,840
And by the way, who even knows
what heaven’s thinking?

69
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:18,720
I forgot how pointless it is
to argue with you.

70
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,880
Well, what about that shaman?

71
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,640
Did you learn anything more about him?

72
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:26,400
We’re looking into it.

73
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:31,040
I’m certain he’s not from our school.

74
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:39,240
Niran.

75
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,440
Do you think we’ll get Qi Rong?

76
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:56,200
I know this isn’t the best option there is.

77
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,200
But they’re our only option right now.

78
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:02,200
Bottoms up!

79
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,360
- Hurry up!
- Come on, Tao!

80
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:07,040
No matter how hard this is,

81
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,920
we have to believe in them.

82
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,880
Especially in Pete, right?

83
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,000
Can you hurry up and get in here?

84
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:27,880
I’m working on that!

85
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,960
Take it easy, dude!

86
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:30,560
Crap! Hurry up!

87
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:32,040
Jack, it’s your turn!

88
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:34,520
The world must be turning upside down.

89
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:39,720
Kids these days don’t care a whit for booze!

90
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:42,880
I just don’t freaking get it.

91
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:45,480
But I’m drinking right here with you.

92
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,760
You’re not a kid anymore.

93
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,200
That’s so mean.

94
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,920
I don’t get why you like it, either.

95
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,680
It just makes you drunk.

96
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,960
What would a kid like you even know?

97
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:03,640
Nature never means for us humans
to be sober all the time.

98
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:09,120
Well, a kid like me
grew up with an alcoholic dad

99
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,280
who gets violent every time he drinks.

100
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:17,200
Hey.

101
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,320
It’s not always like that.

102
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,920
Some people do get violent when
they’re drunk and cause problems.

103
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:24,160
But me?

104
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:26,840
I’m just having fun.

105
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,760
Come on, man.

106
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:32,799
Yeah.

107
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:35,799
As for me…

108
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,640
I’m just a sleepyhead when I’m drunk.

109
00:08:40,159 --> 00:08:40,559
Oh?

110
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:41,840
Tong?

111
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,640
Dude!

112
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,920
What a nuisance.

113
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,080
Why don’t you just sleep on the couch?

114
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,640
Just let him be.

115
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,480
What do you expect from a sleeping man?

116
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:53,960
He’s lost control now.

117
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:00,720
Shit!

118
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:02,800
What’s that, unc?

119
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,080
What’s going on?

120
00:09:16,680 --> 00:09:18,520
Niran, we’ve messed up!

121
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,000
What?

122
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:20,120
What do you mean?

123
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,760
We forgot to put a talisman on Pete before bed!

124
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:24,880
Did he fall asleep?

125
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,440
- Holy crap!
- Holy crap!

126
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,160
Pete.

127
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:54,360
The stairs are freaking right there, man.

128
00:09:57,640 --> 00:09:58,960
I don’t think that’s Pete.

129
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,080
Grab him!

130
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,360
Well, shit!

131
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:33,920
He did it.

132
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:34,600
Me?

133
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,400
I didn’t do it!

134
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:38,280
Pete!

135
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:39,760
Come on!

136
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:45,800
Pete!

137
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:46,440
Pete!

138
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:55,000
What’s going on?

139
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,160
Did he lose control of the demon?

140
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,560
He didn’t lose control.

141
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,000
But he can’t do that in his sleep.

142
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,920
No one can!

143
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:05,120
The right way to go about it is putting
a seal on him before he goes to bed.

144
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,000
We didn’t do that!

145
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,440
Why didn’t you say this sooner?

146
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,200
It slipped my damn mind.

147
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,040
We need to seal him back right now.

148
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,400
We just undid the seal a few hours ago
and now we’re sealing him again?

149
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,320
It can’t be helped!

150
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:17,120
Whatever it is, we need to get him back here.

151
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,640
We’re on it!

152
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:31,440
Niran?

153
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:32,720
Niran?

154
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,120
What are you doing?

155
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,560
The demon’s far gone.

156
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,760
Those three can’t catch up with him now.

157
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:53,960
We have to do something.

158
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:56,440
What are you thinking?

159
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:07,560
Pete!

160
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:09,840
Tao, follow him!

161
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,440
On it!

162
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,200
Follow him!

163
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:16,720
Pete!

164
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:22,640
What now?

165
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:29,400
Get in there! Hurry up!

166
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,200
- Crap!
- Crap!

167
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:37,840
What do we do?

168
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,240
Just get him!

169
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,240
I’m aiming!

170
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:47,600
Tao!

171
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:49,880
I got him!

172
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,200
Keep going and hurry up!

173
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:53,280
Go!

174
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:56,600
Jack!

175
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,240
That hurts like hell.

176
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,120
You okay?

177
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,200
What the hell?

178
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:09,480
Crap!

179
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:12,680
Run!

180
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:13,200
- Crap!
- Crap!

181
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:17,480
- Crap!
- Crap!

182
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:22,800
What do we do?

183
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,960
Pete, what’s wrong with you?

184
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:08,920
Are you really not gonna stop him?

185
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:11,160
Why don’t you do it?

186
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,000
He listens to you more than he does me.

187
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:17,560
That’s nonsense.

188
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:57,840
Hey, Pete.

189
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,280
Pete.

190
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:00,440
Pete.

191
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:02,800
Pete.

192
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:03,800
Shit!

193
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,680
What’s happened?

194
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,200
Who the hell beat your asses?

195
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,200
You did!

196
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:13,000
What?

197
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:16,640
The demon took control of you in your sleep.

198
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:19,800
There ought to be a talisman
on you when you’re sleeping.

199
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,440
But it slipped our minds.

200
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:26,200
In our defense, this isn’t a ritual
we get to perform every day.

201
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,600
It’s our first time.

202
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:31,360
So I need a talisman on me
every time I sleep?

203
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,720
Niran sorted that out with something else.

204
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:50,960
A soul binding ritual?

205
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:54,040
When two souls are bound,

206
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:57,680
half of a person’s spiritual energy
will flow into the other.

207
00:15:58,240 --> 00:16:03,120
Niran’s spiritual energy is suppressing
the demon that nearly devoured you,

208
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:06,400
and it will protect you from now on.

209
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,880
Is that a good thing?

210
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:13,680
I guess it is.

211
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,400
It’s just not something people do.

212
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:22,000
Because you and Niran will have to share
the same fate from here on out.

213
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:25,600
Be that good or bad,

214
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:28,320
the two of you can no longer be
separated from each other

215
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,720
till death do you part.

216
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,720
I’ve known Niran my whole life.

217
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,440
He’s not the type of person
who would do something like this.

218
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,320
What happened to you?

219
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,840
You were fine last night, Niran.

220
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,680
What did you just call me?

221
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,000
It’s me, Jack.

222
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:09,160
Shit!

223
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:17,000
I could have sworn Jack was you just now.

224
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,120
What the hell?

225
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,400
I’m Thua.

226
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:22,560
What the hell’s wrong with you?

227
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:26,840
Shit!

228
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,200
Niran?

229
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,640
I’m Tao, bro.

230
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,360
Did you hit your head?

231
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:43,960
What?

232
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,200
Shit.

233
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:52,400
Shit, shit, shit, what the shit?

234
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:53,720
Shit!

235
00:18:59,200 --> 00:18:59,800
Shit!

236
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,120
What the hell got into him?

237
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:19,560
Niran.

238
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,840
What are you doing here?

239
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:24,920
How the hell did I find you anyway?

240
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:27,280
Well…

241
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:32,920
Half of my spiritual energy flows in you.

242
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,320
I guess the two halves could
communicate somehow.

243
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:45,600
We even want the same drink
at the same time…

244
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,840
How come everyone has your face?

245
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:01,080
You’ll have to put up with it for a bit.

246
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:03,720
It’s the side effect of the ritual.

247
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,160
It’ll probably be gone in a few days.

248
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:09,000
And then what?

249
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:13,920
Fei… didn’t fill you in on
what the ritual entails?

250
00:20:13,920 --> 00:20:14,880
I know that already.

251
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,720
But I mean…

252
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:21,320
Between us…

253
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:22,960
What about it?

254
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:28,920
Well, it’s a ritual for couples, right?

255
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:29,760
So…

256
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,800
You and me…

257
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,760
Am I gonna start having feelings
for you or what?

258
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:37,680
What the hell are you even thinking?

259
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,120
You idiot.

260
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:41,560
It’s a soul binding ritual,

261
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:42,760
not a love potion.

262
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:44,600
It doesn’t work like that.

263
00:20:45,800 --> 00:20:46,280
Yep.

264
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:52,000
But Fei said you were preparing
those dolls for a couple.

265
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:52,960
Oh.

266
00:20:54,040 --> 00:20:54,520
Well…

267
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,360
They’re already in love.

268
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:00,840
The ritual was supposed to guarantee
they never break up.

269
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:02,480
And one more thing,

270
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:04,920
this ritual is common for everyone.

271
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,720
It doesn’t have to be between lovers.

272
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:10,160
I mean, some enemies do it.

273
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:12,440
They do?

274
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,120
What for?

275
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:18,200
So they know they both
stay on the same path for life.

276
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:23,000
In whatever capacity,
they will never part ways.

277
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:27,080
If one must die, the other must, too.

278
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:47,520
Does that mean you and I
have to die together, too?

279
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:50,400
So live well.

280
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Don’t rush into an early grave.

281
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,320
I’m not ready for that.

282
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:58,600
But still, how come everyone has your face?

283
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:00,560
I told you it will go away soon.

284
00:22:16,760 --> 00:22:18,840
Oh, are you taking it off?

285
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:19,800
Yeah.

286
00:22:20,320 --> 00:22:21,520
What else can I do?

287
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:23,520
You won’t move out of this room.

288
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:24,640
What?

289
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:26,880
It’s you who refuse to pick another room.

290
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:32,800
I think we’re past the point
of fighting for this room.

291
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,440
I think so.

292
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,920
We’re sharing our souls.

293
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,560
What’s the big deal
with sharing a room, right?

294
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:49,400
Thank you, though, for saving me.

295
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:54,920
If you didn’t do it, the demon might
already have taken over my body.

296
00:22:57,240 --> 00:23:00,240
I think you might wanna
save that gratitude for later.

297
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,720
You’ll have to wait a whole while, too.

298
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:09,880
Because this may possibly be
the biggest mistake you and I ever made.

299
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:11,800
Why?

300
00:23:13,840 --> 00:23:15,240
Do you regret it?

301
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,160
No.

302
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:23,040
I don’t think that.

303
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:26,360
You jerk.

304
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,600
Can you not take it the wrong way?

305
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:31,760
Alright.

306
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:32,840
Forget it.

307
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:38,760
I don’t think what I did was a mistake.

308
00:23:39,680 --> 00:23:40,520
I just…

309
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,200
I…

310
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:43,480
I was just—

311
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,000
Yeah.

312
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:46,200
You don’t need to explain.

313
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:50,480
If I said I get it, then I get it.

314
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:56,280
I can tell just from the look in your eyes

315
00:23:57,440 --> 00:23:59,360
that you would never hurt me.

316
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:12,800
You trust people too easily.

317
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:14,640
Not just anyone.

318
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:22,960
Oh, the room looks so much better now.

319
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:30,600
I mean, without this ugly tape, it sure does.

320
00:24:56,840 --> 00:24:59,280
Does this mean…

321
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:02,480
We’re sharing a life now?

322
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:07,080
Yes.

323
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:11,120
Our fates. Our souls.

324
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:13,360
Yeah.

325
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,840
Joys and sorrows…

326
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:20,840
Yeah.

327
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:22,600
You can say that.

328
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:26,800
That leaves…

329
00:25:28,960 --> 00:25:29,920
Your money—

330
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:30,360
No.

331
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,480
Oh, wow.

332
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,520
You didn’t even hesitate, you jerk.

333
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:37,440
Don’t be funny, you fool.

334
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,080
Pay attention.

335
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,760
Tell me when you hear Qi Rong.

336
00:25:58,400 --> 00:26:01,080
Focus on Qi Rong and not the sound
of random motorcycles, alright?

337
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:02,400
Damn it.

338
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:04,440
I’m not an idiot.

339
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:05,960
You jerk.

340
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,080
How is it?

341
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:20,680
Did you hear anything?

342
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:40,080
Pete found where Qi Rong is.

343
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:41,560
Now…

344
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,280
We have to choose when to perform the ritual.

345
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:48,560
The most perfect time would be…

346
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:53,480
Month of the Dog, Day of the Cow, and…

347
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:54,680
Hour of the Dragon.

348
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,440
The timing indicates ‘total control.’

349
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:57,640
I think that is the perfect timing.

350
00:27:58,200 --> 00:27:59,920
We can’t just rely on the Earth element.

351
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:00,880
That’s not good.

352
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:03,440
We need a timing with the Fire element.

353
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,320
Qi Rong is associated with Water.

354
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:08,520
He presents in the form of clouds.

355
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,680
He would defeat Fire.

356
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:11,280
No.

357
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:15,760
When you heard his voice,

358
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:17,200
what did you hear?

359
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:22,720
I heard…

360
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:24,960
Storms.

361
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:28,760
Screams.

362
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,680
And metals clanking.

363
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,440
It sounded like a battlefield.

364
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:35,520
Correct!

365
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,240
Qi Rong was born on the battlefield.

366
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:40,600
His core isn’t Water.

367
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:42,880
It’s Metal.

368
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:47,800
Fire defeats Metal.

369
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:50,840
Then we are looking for the ‘slaying fire’ timing.

370
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,600
If we want to stick with Month of the Dog…

371
00:28:53,880 --> 00:28:55,680
Then we need to move from Day of the Cow…

372
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:57,040
To Day of the Snake.

373
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:59,680
And Hour of the… Horse.

374
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:01,200
I think that’s better.

375
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:04,240
We can defeat it

376
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:09,040
as long as the nine of us act as one soul

377
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:12,640
and fight against it, all the way through.

378
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:17,240
And most importantly, no one is allowed
to leave the ritual before it’s over.

379
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:24,200
You all need to know that in the last stretch
right before we seal it,

380
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:28,760
the demon will make its last-gasp attempt.

381
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:30,440
That’s the toughest part.

382
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:33,160
If we get through it, we get through it.

383
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:34,760
If we don’t…

384
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:38,160
We’re dead.

385
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:53,360
We have that, too.

386
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:00,840
Our last-gasp attempt.

387
00:30:05,960 --> 00:30:06,520
Hell yeah!

388
00:30:06,560 --> 00:30:07,120
Put it in!

389
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:08,360
Put it in!

390
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:08,920
Hurry up!

391
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:09,880
Put it in.

392
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,000
Come on.

393
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:11,720
Put it in.

394
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:12,120
Hurry up, Pete.

395
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:12,720
Come on here.

396
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:14,240
Hurry up.

397
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:15,560
Hurry up.

398
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:16,200
Put it in.

399
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:19,840
One, two, three—Hey!

400
00:30:24,960 --> 00:30:25,560
Who?

401
00:30:25,920 --> 00:30:26,600
The Wu.

402
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,840
This will open your third eye.

403
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:53,600
You will all be able
to see Qi Rong from now on.

404
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:07,560
Even if this is defying heaven,

405
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,320
it’s necessary, isn’t it?

406
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:11,960
Maybe a little.

407
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,640
I’m sure heaven doesn’t mind.

408
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:18,200
Here.

409
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:20,480
Take it.

410
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:21,640
One for each of you.

411
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:23,160
Put it on.

412
00:31:25,560 --> 00:31:25,880
Got it.

413
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:30,440
Hold on.

414
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:33,320
Isn’t this the mark of a sacrifice?

415
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:35,240
It is.

416
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:35,960
What?

417
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:39,800
Would Qi Rong show his damn face
for us to seal without some sacrifices?

418
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:42,840
And that is your job for today.

419
00:31:46,960 --> 00:31:48,240
He won’t sacrifice you guys for real.

420
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,480
You’re just baits to lure the demon out.

421
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:52,680
You’ll be fine.

422
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:54,760
He’s right.

423
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:57,720
Because if anyone’s life is at risk today,

424
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:58,760
it’s yours.

425
00:31:59,480 --> 00:31:59,760
What?

426
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:03,520
You’re our lightning rod.

427
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:06,840
What does that mean?

428
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,800
When Qi Rong gets here,

429
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:11,160
while he’s struggling against
our effort to seal him,

430
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:13,920
he will release a tremendous
amount of energy.

431
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,280
You must absorb that energy
to make sure everyone is safe,

432
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:18,400
especially Niran.

433
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:21,080
Why me?

434
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,600
Because you have a demon within you.

435
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:26,440
You’re the strongest person here.

436
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:31,360
Fine.

437
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:33,240
What do I have to do?

438
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:35,760
Crap.

439
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:39,920
Why do I look even more like
a sacrifice than these three idiots?

440
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:45,920
These chains will attract most of
Qi Rong’s energy and transfer it to you.

441
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:49,960
The demon in you will
slowly negate that energy.

442
00:32:50,600 --> 00:32:52,600
Your job is to put up with it.

443
00:32:53,280 --> 00:32:54,440
And if I can’t?

444
00:32:54,560 --> 00:32:55,200
You’re dead.

445
00:32:55,560 --> 00:32:55,880
What?

446
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:58,600
Dead?

447
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:04,600
Pete.

448
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:07,280
Your soul are bound to mine.

449
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,520
If you die, I die.

450
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:13,240
So I’m not gonna let that happen.

451
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,400
Don’t baby him.

452
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:17,840
I’ll be honest.

453
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:19,960
When sealing a demon,

454
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:22,040
the person whose life is the most at risk

455
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:24,120
is the bait like him.

456
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:25,080
What?

457
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,720
You know you can just keep your mouth
shut if you have nothing nice to say?

458
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:30,520
Someone gotta tell him the statistics.

459
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:00,000
It will protect you.

460
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:09,159
You will get through it safe and sound.

461
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:11,199
Trust me on this.

462
00:34:30,040 --> 00:34:30,679
You all will.

463
00:34:32,040 --> 00:34:33,000
We will get through this together.

464
00:34:54,159 --> 00:35:00,400
The Great Lord Warrior
whose reputation precedes him.

465
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:09,360
Please accept this offering
bestowing with blood and souls.

466
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,680
Please reside upon this stable throne.

467
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,480
Qi Rong.

468
00:35:26,840 --> 00:35:29,160
Please reside!

469
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:32,680
Please reside!

470
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:37,960
Qi Rong.

471
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:41,040
Present yourself!

472
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:44,600
Present yourself!

473
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:49,960
Qi Rong.

474
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:52,880
Come accept your offering

475
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:56,040
- …right this moment!
- …right this moment!

476
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:49,720
It really is Metal.

477
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:55,680
Evil forces, be sealed upon this throne

478
00:36:56,120 --> 00:37:00,080
as if decreed by heaven!

479
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:25,760
His energy is contained!

480
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,360
The sealing has begun.

481
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:34,720
Keep going!

482
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:35,600
I can do this!

483
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:21,720
Thua?

484
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:22,280
Tao?

485
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:25,640
Niran?

486
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,120
It got us, didn’t it?

487
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:46,200
Fog?

488
00:38:47,160 --> 00:38:48,720
From all the legends
we’ve been researching,

489
00:38:49,680 --> 00:38:53,200
Qi Rong’s strongest power is
his manipulation of fog.

490
00:38:53,680 --> 00:38:56,200
Then how do we fight it?

491
00:38:58,480 --> 00:38:59,760
Whatever happens,

492
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:03,120
we have to continue with the ritual.

493
00:39:49,600 --> 00:39:50,640
Pete!

494
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:52,480
Niran!

495
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:27,760
Crap!

496
00:40:28,480 --> 00:40:29,200
Tao?

497
00:40:29,520 --> 00:40:30,520
Yeah, it’s me.

498
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:31,920
You’re the first person I found!

499
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:33,800
Tao!

500
00:40:35,720 --> 00:40:36,520
Thua?

501
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:38,840
You guys are the first I ran into.

502
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:41,120
If we follow the sound of the drum,

503
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,560
maybe we can find
our way back to everyone.

504
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:45,480
I bet!

505
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:47,720
You remember what they said?

506
00:40:48,040 --> 00:40:51,760
If we all stick together and complete
the ritual, we’ll make it.

507
00:40:52,120 --> 00:40:52,880
That’s not all.

508
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:55,040
- Pete.
- Pete.

509
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:01,160
We’re locked in here by the demon.

510
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:04,480
The only way to clear this fog

511
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:06,520
is to give the demon a sacrifice.

512
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:14,520
That is your job.

513
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:24,160
Hey!

514
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:26,400
Is anyone there?

515
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:54,880
Lapdog!

516
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:57,000
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

517
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:59,000
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

518
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,480
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

519
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:03,720
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

520
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:04,960
LAPDOG!
WITHOUT THE STRINGS,
YOU’RE JUST A WORTHLESS PUPPET.

521
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:06,080
SCUMBAG
BEST LAPDOG AWARDS

522
00:42:06,520 --> 00:42:08,200
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

523
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:10,080
GOVERNMENT LAPDOG
LAPDOG!

524
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,280
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

525
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:12,800
- Lapdog!
- Lapdog!

526
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:13,760
- Lapdog!

527
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:27,120
Wu Yong Le!

528
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:03,720
Who?

529
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:04,840
The Wu.

530
00:44:21,880 --> 00:44:22,640
Niran.

531
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:24,360
Why aren’t you wearing this?

532
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:26,360
I designed it.

533
00:44:26,520 --> 00:44:27,280
Everyone’s wearing it.

534
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:30,960
Well, look at it.

535
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:32,400
It’s lame as hell.

536
00:44:32,480 --> 00:44:33,000
Who’d want to wear that?

537
00:44:33,040 --> 00:44:33,440
Hey.

538
00:44:34,320 --> 00:44:35,600
Take it back.

539
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:38,040
It’s cool as hell.

540
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:40,600
If you think it’s cool,
then it’s even more lame.

541
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:41,400
What the hell is that?

542
00:44:42,040 --> 00:44:43,320
Why do you put ‘the’ in front of ‘Wu’?

543
00:44:46,160 --> 00:44:46,480
Look.

544
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:49,920
What?

545
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:52,360
From the back, it asks, “Who?”

546
00:44:52,960 --> 00:44:53,880
As in, “Who am I?”

547
00:44:54,520 --> 00:44:55,360
Then you turn around…

548
00:44:58,360 --> 00:44:59,320
“I’m The Wu!”

549
00:45:01,240 --> 00:45:02,520
Now you wanna put it on, huh?

550
00:45:02,880 --> 00:45:04,960
I’ve thought everything through, man.

551
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:06,160
I doubt it. I bet you just came up with that.

552
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:07,400
It was intentional, idiot.

553
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:08,080
Look.

554
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:10,560
Would it look so cool otherwise?

555
00:45:10,720 --> 00:45:11,400
This is nonsense.

556
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:12,040
Put it on.

557
00:45:12,280 --> 00:45:13,040
The hell I would.

558
00:45:13,080 --> 00:45:15,280
- Put it on!
- The hell, man? No way!

559
00:45:15,680 --> 00:45:16,040
Put it on!

560
00:45:16,040 --> 00:45:16,400
Pete!

561
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:18,880
- It’s teamwork, dude!
- Don’t make me hit you with a trophy!

562
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:20,320
Careful with that! That’s mine!

563
00:45:20,480 --> 00:45:21,480
- You put it on right now.
- It’s not cool!

564
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:22,720
It is cool!

565
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:23,800
Put it on, you idiot!

566
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:24,600
Take off your shirt!

567
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:30,640
Handsome as hell.

568
00:45:31,440 --> 00:45:32,200
The Wu.

569
00:45:32,720 --> 00:45:33,840
We are The Wu!

570
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,200
Crap, this might be too cool.

571
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:37,600
So damn cool.

572
00:45:38,280 --> 00:45:38,600
Well?

573
00:45:39,400 --> 00:45:40,720
You happy now?

574
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:41,680
Hold on.

575
00:45:43,280 --> 00:45:43,960
Let’s take a photo.

576
00:45:45,120 --> 00:45:45,760
We’re just really cool.

577
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:47,520
Come on here.

578
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:50,800
Here. This angle is better.

579
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:54,040
One, two, three.

580
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:57,640
Hey, don’t cover up the logo!

581
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:58,840
The Wu! Teamwork!

582
00:45:59,040 --> 00:45:59,880
Why aren’t you working
with the team, man?

583
00:45:59,920 --> 00:46:01,440
Just be happy I even put it on.

584
00:46:01,600 --> 00:46:02,640
Why are we even taking photos?

585
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:04,480
Don’t mess it up.

586
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:05,040
Come on.

587
00:46:05,240 --> 00:46:06,280
One, two, three.

588
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:19,360
If we back down now, that means…

589
00:46:20,000 --> 00:46:21,600
the demon wins, right?

590
00:46:27,840 --> 00:46:29,600
At this point, it is undeniable that

591
00:46:31,640 --> 00:46:32,920
what we’re going to do

592
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:35,600
is nothing short of life-threatening.
